on your own domain.

00:13:59.870 --> 00:14:07.150
So if you are using Google Apps,
you are able to map end

00:14:07.150 --> 00:14:09.160
applications on Google
App Engine to

00:14:09.160 --> 00:14:10.860
your Google Apps domain.

00:14:10.860 --> 00:14:14.430
And so I just took advantage
of this feature.

00:14:14.430 --> 00:14:19.110
And so if you're a Google Apps
customer, and you have a

00:14:19.110 --> 00:14:25.440
verified domain, then you can
simply publish this website to

00:14:25.440 --> 00:14:26.690
your own domain.

00:14:28.850 --> 00:14:32.450
And it's not really doing
any copy stuff.

00:14:32.450 --> 00:14:37.340
It will just tell our
application that if someone

00:14:37.340 --> 00:14:45.370
goes to this domain, it will put
some proxy stuff to solve

00:14:45.370 --> 00:14:49.610
the pages from Google Drive
but it will look as if it

00:14:49.610 --> 00:14:53.890
would come from your
own custom domain.

00:14:53.890 --> 00:14:56.510
So that's quite nice, because
you can make changes on your

00:14:56.510 --> 00:15:01.160
website and they will instantly
be visible right on

00:15:01.160 --> 00:15:02.980
your domain.

00:15:02.980 --> 00:15:08.364
And so if anybody's interested,
this example--

00:15:08.364 --> 00:15:09.810
now it's live.

00:15:09.810 --> 00:15:15.030
